    "(89)Here we have used n µ (k) ≡ ⟨ d † µ dµ ⟩ ψ0 ∈ {0, 1} to denote the occupation of the singleparticle states in the Slater determinant |ψ 0 ⟩.If we denote the form factors of the HF orbitals as Λ µν (k, q) = τ sab (ψ τ as µ (k)) * ψ τ bs ν (k + q)λ τ,ab (k, q), where λ τ,ab are the single-particle form factors defined in Eq. 16, the linearized TDHF equation (84) for MA-TBG can then be written as following generalized eigenvalue equation(n µ (k + q) -n ν (k))φ m q,µν (k)η q,m ω q,m = |E µ (k + q) -E ν (k)|φ m q,µν (k) (90) + 1 A G V (q + G) k ′ ∈mBZ tr φ m q (k ′)Λ(k ′, q + G) Λ † (k, q + G) µν - 1 A q ′ ∈all V (q ′) Λ(k + q, q ′)φ m q (k + q ′)Λ † (k, q ′) µν,where η q,m ∈ {-1, +1} is defined such that ω q,m ≥ 0.",
